hopobject.body: I'd like some euros abingdonmedicalmuseum.com The MTA earlier this year proposed canceling a shuttle service it has provided to Bronx bus drivers for the last 15 years. A transit official estimated the service costs about $270,000 a year. Union officials said the cost estimate was grossly exaggerated. The bus drivers periodically are taken by car from their routes back to the depots so they can pick their next work assignment based on seniority.
